{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Scrap and replace the Marginal Pricing Model for UK Energy",
        "additional_details": "Wholesale price of electricity is set by the most expensive unit of generation needed to meet demand, almost always gas-fired power. When 60\u201370% of the grid is supplied by cheaper renewables and nuclear, households/businesses still pay prices tied to volatile global gas markets.\r\n \r\nWe think the Economic/Social Benefits of Reform could be:\r\nLower Consumer Bills\r\nBoost to Disposable Income\r\nEnergy Security & Inflation Control\r\nGreen Jobs boosted\r\nTackles Fuel Poverty\r\nPublic Health\r\nAccelerates Net Zero\r\nLower Carbon Footprint\r\n",
        "background": "Scrap and replace the Marginal Pricing Model for a fairer pricing structure with lower consumer and business energy bills. The UK is free to set its market rules post-Brexit. We think this change would cut bills, stabilise the economy, protect households, and secure the UK\u2019s long-term energy future.",
